      "note": "Lit., \"after your death\". The expression mawt does not always denote physical death. Arab philologists - e.g., Raghib - explain the verb mata (lit., \"he died\") as having, in certain contexts, the meaning of \"he became deprived of sensation, dead as to the senses\"; and occasionally as \"deprived of the intellectual faculty, intellectually dead\"; and sometimes even as \"he slept\" (see Lane VII, 2741)."
